wikipedia_page.main: Eleanor Constance Lodge  (18 September 1869, Hanley, Staffordshire – 19 March 1936) was a British academic who served as Vice-Principal of Lady Margaret Hall, Oxford from 1906 to 1921 and then Principal of Westfield College, Hampstead, in the University of London, from 1921 to 1931.
